{"cursor":"12805","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n\nThe 'biretta' () is a square cap with three or four peaks or horns, sometimes\nsurmounted by a tuft. Traditionally the three peaked biretta is worn by Roman\nCatholic clergy and some Anglican and Lutheran clergy. The four peaked biretta\nis worn as academic dress by those holding a doctoral degree from a pontifical\nfaculty or pontifical university. Occasionally the biretta is worn by advocates\nin law courts, for instance the advocates in the Channel Islands.\n","linknr":247,"url":"Biretta","recorded":1362566450,"links":40,"instances":["term","priest","color","catholicism"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Anglican vestments","College of Cardinals","Eucharistic vestments","History of clothing (Europe)","History of clothing (Western fashion)","History of clothing","History of fashion","Lutheran vestments","Religious headwear","Roman Catholic vestments"],"headings":["Origins","Liturgical biretta","Academic biretta","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cc/Biret.JPG/220px-Biret.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Bonete_Sammlung_Philippi.JPG/125px-Bonete_Sammlung_Philippi.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/AngeloScola.22-03-2009.jpg/133px-AngeloScola.22-03-2009.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Procession_of_the_Precious_Blood_of_Jesus_Christ-Bruges%3B_nederlandse_Bisschop_50.JPG/77px-Procession_of_the_Precious_Blood_of_Jesus_Christ-Bruges%3B_nederlandse_Bisschop_50.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Rector_univ.jpg/220px-Rector_univ.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf1